Christ Love Rhema Chapel International has started its annual 51-day fasting and prayer. The programme, tagged ‘Supernatural Lifting’, which kicked off on January 13, is expected to end on March 14, 2022. The event had been holding at Christ Love Rhema Chapel International, behind Gabaak Petrol Station, Opposite Nasfat Mosque, Akos-Olori, Old Ijebu-Ode Road, Ikorodu Town, Lagos State. Soul Winning Is A Great Task (II) PFN President, Odesola, For INL Thanksgiving Commenting on the programme, the hosts, Pastors Yemi and Sarah Isaac, asked participants to come with their expectations from God for a direction that would lead them to testimonies. He said: “When people are down, confused, depressed, have broken homes or marriages, troubled finances, business failure, they need anointing, divine direction information that will bring about divine lifting. “There are other gains that your heart is yearning for that will change your life and bring about restoration. That is the significance of this year’s 51-day fasting and prayer programme.”